w=860 430w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/66479/1651338975-headless-cms-img2.jpg?auto=format&w=860 860w","sizes":"(min-width: 860px) 860px, 100vw"}},"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpg;base64,"},"width":860,"height":430},"alt":"headless-cms-img2"}}],"links":[],"value":{"schema":"dast","document":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"type":"span","value":"What is the Headless CMS?"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Before the explain,  Let's talk about what does the headless CMS exactly mean.\nIn the headless CMS, "},{"type":"span","marks":["strong","underline"],"value":"Headless"},{"type":"span","value":" represents "},{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"tearing down the \"head\"(frontend) from the \"body\"(backend)"},{"type":"span","value":". CMS stands for Content Management System which literally means the system that manages contents."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"type":"span","value":"Traditional CMS"}]},{"item":"9976570","type":"block"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"In traditional CMS, It is so tight that the connection between the system that serves contents and the contents that contained by the system, it's not that easy displaying the same contents to other services such as other web or apps. Namely, "},{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"the transplant of the contents was difficult"},{"type":"span","value":"."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"children":[{"type":"span","value":"Headless CMS"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"The headless CMS could be divided into few major parts. Let me explain with my "},{"url":"https://www.gatsbyjs.com/","meta":[{"id":"target","value":"_blank"}],"type":"link","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Gatsby"}]},{"type":"span","value":" blog and DatoCMS which is the headless CMS used in my blog."}]},{"type":"list","style":"bulleted","children":[{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"The frontend codes"},{"type":"span","value":"(Gatsby)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"The contents posted on the blog"},{"type":"span","value":"(DatoCMS)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"CMS to frontend communication method"},{"type":"span","value":"(GraphQL)"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"You can select the frontend framework whatever you want because the frontend codes just need to draw how to show the contents. Since the contents which are posted on the blog are managed by external CMS, the contents and the frontend codes are completely separated. "}]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"type":"span","value":"How does the Headless CMS work?"}]},{"item":"10393792","type":"block"},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Then, how do we get the contents from CMS when we deploy the blog? "},{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"Generally"},{"type":"span","value":", as you may thought, it can be done with "},{"type":"span","marks":["highlight"],"value":"RESTful API or GraphQL"},{"type":"span","value":". Posting the new content procedure progresses through the following steps."}]},{"type":"list","style":"numbered","children":[{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Writing new contents on the CMS"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Deploying the blog("},{"type":"span","marks":["code"],"value":"npm run deploy"},{"type":"span","value":", etc.)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Getting contents from CMS while generate static web page"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Complete deploying static web page blog(Gatsby, Jekyll, etc.) "}]}]}]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"children":[{"type":"span","value":"Convenience hidden behind a spooky term"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"Headless.. 뭔가 공포 영화에 나올 법한 단어였지만 headless CMS는 결국 블로그와 같은 사이트 운영을 더욱 유연하고 편리하게 해주는 멋진 도구였습니다! 여러분도 혹시 블로그를 운영하실 계획이 있으시다면 headless CMS를 활용하여 멋지고 편리한 자신만의 블로그를 꾸려나가 보시길 바랍니다!"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"span","value":"We are not getting scared by the word \"Headless\" anymore unless we saw that on real life!🤣 After all, the headless CMS is a great tool for people who wants to manage blogs or something with flexibility and conveniently. If you are planning to manage new blogs, make fascinating blogs with the headless CMS!"}]},{"item":"10536677","type":"block"}]}}}}},"pageContext":{"id":"6607939","locale":"en"}},
